From 9aef1d61f98ba8f1408365430889a570db1f53be Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sen Wang <sen@ti.com>
Date: Mon, 23 Mar 2026 00:10:42 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 5/5] Documentation: sound: Add TAS675x codec mixer controls
 documentation

Add documentation for the TAS6754-Q1 codec driver ALSA mixer controls.

Documents the three DSP signal path modes (Normal, Low Latency Path,
Full Feature Low Latency Path) with their respective feature trade-offs,
all volume controls with ramping behavior, auto-mute and silence
detection thresholds, hardware protection features (over-temperature,
overcurrent), and the three types of load diagnostics (DC, AC, and
real-time monitoring during playback).

Includes practical usage examples for common operations such as DSP mode
switching, triggering load diagnostics, and reading fault status, along
with troubleshooting guidance for diagnostic failures.

Signed-off-by: Sen Wang <sen@ti.com>
